x^y
(0,\infty)\times\mathbb{R}\to\mathbb{R}
(x,y)\mapsto x^y
(x_n,y_n)
(x,y)
x_n\to x
y_n\to y
\exp
\ln
x^y=\exp(y\ln (x))
 \begin{align*} \lim_{n\to\infty} x_n^{y_n} &=\lim_{n\to\infty} \exp\left(y_n\ln(x_n)\right)\\ &= \exp\left(\lim_{n\to\infty}y_n\ln(x_n)\right)\\ &= \exp\left(\lim_{n\to\infty}y_n\ln\left(\lim_{n\to\infty}x_n\right)\right)\\ &= \exp\left(y\ln(x)\right)=x^y? \end{align*} 
